            // array('id' => '104','page_id' => '5','hints' => 'Information section About Button','title' => 'Application Information','subtitle' => 'Intakes, English Language Requirements, Diploma - Advanced Diploma','image' => NULL,'description' => 'International students are anticipated to begin planning for their research in Canada one year in advance. The most important intake for Canada usually is \'Fall\' i.e September. The different intake is in the month of \'Winter\' i.e. January, however, it relies upon the program and the institution. Very few institutes have May intake as well.
                                                                                            
            //                                                                                                     All students have to be fluent in English if they\'re applying to Canadian Institutes. International students want to have a specified degree of English language competence. All students ought to take the IELTS or TOEFL(ibt) exams. An IELTS band of 6.5 for Undergraduate & 6.5/7 for Postgraduate publications or a TOEFL rating of eighty and above for Undergraduate and ninety and above for Post Graduate courses is desirable. For Diploma and Advanced Diploma 6.0 in IELTS or equal different tests, a rating is required.
                                                                                            
